---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import { getCollection, type CollectionEntry } from 'astro:content';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import BrowserMock from '../../components/sections/BrowserMock.astro';
import dashboardShot from '../../assets/images/projects/self-service-dashboard.png';

// Only fully-designed ("published") case studies get a detail page.
export async function getStaticPaths() {
  const projects = await getCollection('portfolio', p => p.data.published);
  return projects.map(p => ({ params: { slug: p.slug }, props: { project: p } }));
}

interface Props { project: CollectionEntry<'portfolio'> }
const { project } = Astro.props;
const { title, description, role, scope, impact, heroImageAlt, nextTitle, nextHref } = project.data;
---

<BaseLayout title={`${title} — Marion Débonnaire`} description={description} bg="white">
  <!-- ░░ Header (gradient) ░░ -->
  <section class="case-header gradient-hero nav-bleed">
    <div class="header-col">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/work">Work</a>
        <span class="sep" aria-hidden="true">/</span>
        <span class="current">{title}</span>
      </nav>
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      <p class="lead">{description}</p>
    </div>
    <div class="header-col meta-col">
      <dl class="meta">
        <div><dt>ROLE</dt><dd>{role}</dd></div>
        <div><dt>SCOPE</dt><dd>{scope}</dd></div>
        <div><dt>IMPACT</dt><dd class="accent">{impact}</dd></div>
      </dl>
    </div>
    <div class="header-pad"></div>
  </section>

  <!-- ░░ Hero screenshot in a MacBook frame ░░ -->
  <div class="laptop">
    <div class="screen">
      <div class="camera"><span></span></div>
      <div class="screen-inner">
        {project.slug === 'toucan-ai'
          ? <BrowserMock variant="chart" />
          : <Image src={dashboardShot} alt={heroImageAlt ?? title} widths={[640, 968, 1400]} sizes="(max-width: 1040px) 92vw, 968px" />}
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="base-1"></div>
    <div class="base-2"><div class="notch"></div></div>
  </div>

  {project.slug === 'self-service-dashboard' && (
  <Fragment>
  <!-- ░░ 01 · My Role ░░ -->
  <section class="prose">
    <div class="sec-head"><span class="num">01</span><h2>My Role</h2></div>
    <p class="p-lg">Senior Product Manager. I led this initiative end-to-end, from discovery to delivery, working closely with a Lead Engineer and a Product Designer. I was responsible for framing the problem, defining the product strategy, making prioritization calls, and ensuring we shipped fast enough to unlock business impact.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ░░ 02 · The Problem ░░ -->
  <section class="prose">
    <div class="sec-head"><span class="num">02</span><h2>The Problem</h2></div>
    <p>The absence of a self-service offering represented a <strong>significant amount of lost revenue every year</strong>. For most of our prospects, self-service was a non-negotiable prerequisite to even consider Toucan, making it a critical acquisition blocker.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- What we heard -->
  <section class="prose tight">
    <div class="eyebrow">WHAT WE HEARD</div>
    <blockquote class="pull-quote">
      <p>"As a B2B SaaS, I need a self-service layer in my product so that admin users can build their own dashboards with a simple, point-and-click experience, without depending on my team."</p>
      <cite>Toucan prospect, 2025</cite>
    </blockquote>
    <p class="follow">Self-service had been one of our most recurring requests from prospects, and its absence had been causing us to regularly miss deals.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Who needed it -->
  <section class="wide">
    <div class="wide-intro">
      <div class="eyebrow">WHO NEEDED IT</div>
      <h3>Three distinct user needs</h3>
      <p>Through customer interviews, we identified three segments with different expectations:</p>
    </div>
    <div class="needs-grid">
      <div class="need"><div class="frac">1/3</div><p>want to <strong>browse and select</strong> charts from an existing library</p></div>
      <div class="need"><div class="frac">1/3</div><p>want to <strong>edit and create</strong> charts themselves</p></div>
      <div class="need"><div class="frac">1/3</div><p>want to <strong>edit the underlying data</strong></p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Use cases -->
  <section class="wide">
    <div class="wide-intro">
      <div class="eyebrow">PAIN POINTS</div>
      <h3>Use cases</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="uc-grid">
      <div class="uc"><div class="eyebrow">AS AN END USER</div><p>I can only view the dashboard my vendor has set up. If I need something specific, I have to submit a request and wait. I can't iterate on my own.</p></div>
      <div class="uc"><div class="eyebrow">AS AN ADMIN</div><p>I have to handle every customization request manually. I lose time on specific developments, and I have no way to monetize these new options.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ░░ 03 · Approach & Key Decisions ░░ -->
  <section class="prose">
    <div class="sec-head"><span class="num">03</span><h2>Approach &amp; Key Decisions</h2></div>
    <p>Building self-service on top of a decade-old product came with real constraints: significant UX debt, a complex technical foundation, and no room for a long delivery cycle.</p>
    <div class="decision">
      <div class="eyebrow">DECISION 01 · TRADE-OFF</div>
      <h3>Speed over completeness</h3>
      <p>Rather than trying to serve all three user segments at once, we made a deliberate call to address the first two thirds of the demand first.</p>
      <p>We built a pick-and-choose experience: end users can browse a chart library curated by their admin, and select what they want with a simple, point-and-click interface. No technical or data expertise required. This covered the most common use cases immediately, without the complexity of a full self-service editor, and got us to market fast enough to start winning deals.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="decision">
      <div class="eyebrow">DECISION 02 · UX DILEMMA</div>
      <h3>Rebuild or adapt?</h3>
      <p>The ideal path would have been a full redesign of the dashboard creation and editing experience. The existing one carried years of accumulated complexity and technical debt. But a full rebuild would have taken too long, and our primary goal was to equip the Sales team as fast as possible.</p>
      <p>We chose a pragmatic approach: working within the constraints of the existing experience, making targeted improvements, and accepting deliberate compromises. This allowed us to ship a first version significantly faster, without betting everything on a lengthy redesign cycle.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ░░ 04 · The Solution ░░ -->
  <section class="wide">
    <div class="sec-head solution-head"><span class="num">04</span><h2>The Solution</h2></div>
    <div class="solution-block">
      <p>A pick-and-choose dashboard editor that lets business users customize their embedded analytics experience without any technical knowledge. Admins define the chart library; end users build their own views from it, independently.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ░░ 05 · Business Impact ░░ -->
  <section class="wide">
    <div class="sec-head solution-head"><span class="num">05</span><h2>Business Impact</h2></div>
    <div class="impact-grid">
      <div class="impact-card accent">
        <div class="stat">36%</div>
        <p>a determining factor in 36% of SQL-to-QSO conversions in 2025, one of the most impactful features delivered that year.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="impact-card lilac">
        <div class="stat">~20</div>
        <p>clients adopted self-service since launch.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  </Fragment>
  )}

  {project.slug === 'toucan-ai' && (
  <Fragment>
  <!-- ░░ Intro ░░ -->
  <section class="prose">
    <p class="p-lg">Instead of navigating dashboards, end users simply ask questions in natural language and instantly receive clear, reliable answers, complete with charts and narrative. Toucan handles all the underlying complexity: data connections, semantic layer, query generation, chart formatting, and enterprise-grade security.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ░░ 01 · My Role ░░ -->
  <section class="prose">
    <div class="sec-head"><span class="num">01</span><h2>My Role</h2></div>
    <p class="p-lg">Senior Product Manager, responsible for the chart and dashboard creation experience within Toucan AI. Working with my squad, my focus spanned both sides of the product: the maker experience (how builders create and edit charts and dashboards in an AI-native environment) and, above all, the end user experience. Ensuring that asking a question and instantly receiving a relevant, accurate chart would feel as simple and natural as possible.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ░░ 02 · The Problem ░░ -->
  <section class="prose">
    <div class="sec-head"><span class="num">02</span><h2>The Problem</h2></div>
    <div class="decision">
      <h3>The market shift</h3>
      <p>By mid-2025, the pressure was undeniable: AI giants were entering every vertical, competitors were shipping AI features at speed, and end users shaped by tools like ChatGPT expected conversation-first experiences.</p>
      <p>The old analytics paradigm (click, navigate, analyze) was becoming obsolete. <strong>81% of users now prefer asking a question over navigating charts.</strong> SaaS companies without a credible AI analytics offering faced harder sales, higher churn, and mounting pressure from both clients and investors.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="decision">
      <h3>The product challenge</h3>
      <p>Rebuilding around conversational AI raised a fundamental design question: <strong>how should users create and edit charts in an AI-native product?</strong></p>
      <p>Giving full control to AI risked frustrating power users. Keeping a purely manual editing experience would defeat the purpose of going AI-native. The right answer was somewhere in between, and it wasn't obvious.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ░░ 03 · Approach & Key Decisions ░░ -->
  <section class="prose">
    <div class="sec-head"><span class="num">03</span><h2>Approach &amp; Key Decisions</h2></div>
    <div class="decision">
      <div class="eyebrow">DECISION 01 · INTERACTION MODEL</div>
      <h3>Designing for complementary modes</h3>
      <p>Through user testing, a clear pattern emerged: there is no single "right" way to work with AI in analytics. Users defaulted to different behaviors depending on their profile and context.</p>
      <p>A typical PM would use AI to kickstart a chart or dashboard, then switch to manual editing to fine-tune the result. A more technical user might prefer to go directly into code mode for precision. Some users never left the AI interface at all.</p>
      <p>This insight led to a key product decision: <strong>rather than forcing a single interaction model, we designed three complementary editing modes (AI, manual, and code), allowing each user to work the way that felt most natural to them.</strong> The challenge was making these three modes feel like one coherent experience, not three separate tools stitched together.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="decision">
      <div class="eyebrow">DECISION 02 · TRUST</div>
      <h3>Designing for trust in AI</h3>
      <p>Embedding AI into a product used for business decision-making raised a specific UX challenge: <strong>how do you make users trust an AI answer when the stakes are real?</strong></p>
      <p>Analytics are inherently high-stakes. A wrong chart or a misinterpreted metric can lead to poor business decisions. Generic AI responses were not enough.</p>
      <p>To address this, we designed the conversational experience around transparency. Rather than just surfacing an answer, the product exposes its reasoning at every step: which data table was selected and why, which transformation steps were applied, and why a specific chart type was chosen to represent the data. This "chain of thought" layer gave users the context they needed to validate AI outputs with confidence, not just accept them blindly.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="decision">
      <div class="eyebrow">DECISION 03 · TENSION</div>
      <h3>The probabilistic challenge</h3>
      <p>One of the broader challenges the team had to navigate was a fundamental tension at the heart of the product: <strong>analytics is a deterministic domain, but AI is probabilistic by nature.</strong> Users expect exact, reproducible answers from data. AI cannot always guarantee that.</p>
      <p>This made evaluation a critical and complex challenge. Ensuring that the AI's answers were not just plausible, but reliably accurate. While the solution was primarily an engineering and ML challenge, it shaped how we framed requirements and set user expectations throughout the product experience.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ░░ 04 · The Solution ░░ -->
  <section class="wide">
    <div class="sec-head solution-head"><span class="num">04</span><h2>The Solution</h2></div>
    <div class="solution-block">
      <p>A conversational analytics experience embedded directly into SaaS products. End users simply ask a question in natural language and instantly receive the answer: a key figure, a chart, or a breakdown, with no technical knowledge required. For those who want to go further, the interface also supports manual editing and code mode, so every profile can work at their own level of depth.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ░░ 05 · Business Impact ░░ -->
  <section class="wide">
    <div class="sec-head solution-head"><span class="num">05</span><h2>Business Impact</h2></div>
    <div class="impact-grid">
      <div class="impact-card accent">
        <div class="stat">15+</div>
        <p>qualified commercial opportunities generated by the beta launch in its first month.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="impact-card lilac">
        <div class="stat">June '25</div>
        <p>first paying clients onboarded, marking the transition from beta to general availability.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  </Fragment>
  )}

  <!-- Next project -->
  <section class="wide next-wrap">
    <a href={nextHref ?? '#'} class="next-card">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow plain">NEXT PROJECT</div>
        <div class="next-title">{nextTitle}</div>
      </div>
      <div class="next-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
    </a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
/* ── Header ── */
.case-header { display: block; }
.header-col {
  max-width: var(--max-prose-lg);
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding-inline: var(--gutter);
}
.header-col:first-of-type { padding-top: 64px; }
.breadcrumb {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 10px;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 12.5px;
  margin-bottom: 26px;
}
.breadcrumb a { color: var(--color-accent); }
.breadcrumb .sep { color: #b3aec0; }
.breadcrumb .current { color: var(--color-meta); }
.case-header h1 {
  font-size: 62px;
  font-weight: 600;
  line-height: 1.04;
  letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  margin: 0 0 24px;
  color: var(--color-ink);
}
.case-header .lead {
  font-size: 19px;
  line-height: 1.6;
  color: var(--color-muted);
  max-width: 60ch;
  margin: 0;
}
.meta-col { padding-top: 40px; }
.meta {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 28px;
  border-top: 1px solid rgba(21, 19, 28, 0.14);
  padding-top: 26px;
  margin: 0;
}
.meta dt {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  color: var(--color-meta);
  margin-bottom: 9px;
}
.meta dd {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-weight: 600;
  font-size: 17px;
  color: var(--color-ink);
  margin: 0;
}
.meta dd.accent { color: var(--color-accent); }
.header-pad { height: 96px; }

/* ── MacBook frame ── */
.laptop {
  max-width: 1040px;
  margin: -72px auto 0;
  padding: 0 var(--gutter);
  position: relative;
  z-index: 2;
}
.screen {
  max-width: 968px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  background: #0C0B10;
  border-radius: 20px 20px 7px 7px;
  padding: 13px 13px 15px;
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-laptop);
  border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
}
.camera { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; padding: 1px 0 9px; }
.camera span { width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: #26252c; box-shadow: inset 0 0 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); }
.screen-inner { border-radius: 7px; overflow: hidden; background: #fff; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4); }
.screen-inner :global(img) { width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }
.base-1 {
  position: relative;
  height: 16px;
  background: linear-gradient(180deg, #e3e4e9 0%, #c2c3cb 55%, #a7a8b1 100%);
  border-radius: 0 0 4px 4px;
  box-shadow: inset 0 2px 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
}
.base-2 {
  position: relative;
  height: 11px;
  width: 104%;
  margin-left: -2%;
  background: linear-gradient(180deg, #b9bac2 0%, #9a9ba4 60%, #7e7f88 100%);
  border-radius: 0 0 14px 14px;
  box-shadow: 0 14px 22px -10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
}
.base-2 .notch {
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  width: 128px;
  height: 9px;
  background: linear-gradient(180deg, #86878f, #aeb0b8);
  border-radius: 0 0 9px 9px;
}

/* ── Prose columns ── */
.prose { max-width: var(--max-prose); margin: 0 auto; padding: 92px var(--gutter) 0; }
.prose.tight { padding-top: 56px; }
.sec-head {
  display: flex;
  align-items: baseline;
  gap: 14px;
  border-bottom: var(--border-hairline);
  padding-bottom: 20px;
  margin-bottom: 28px;
}
.sec-head .num {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-weight: 600;
  font-size: 19px;
  color: var(--color-accent);
  letter-spacing: -0.01em;
}
.sec-head h2 {
  font-size: 34px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: -0.025em;
  color: var(--color-ink);
  margin: 0;
  line-height: 1.05;
}
.prose p { font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.75; color: var(--color-body-soft); margin: 0; }
.prose p.p-lg { font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-body); }
.prose p strong { font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink); }

.eyebrow {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  color: var(--color-accent);
  margin-bottom: 14px;
}
.pull-quote { margin: 0; padding: 8px 0 8px 28px; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent); }
.pull-quote p {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-weight: 500;
  font-size: 24px;
  line-height: 1.45;
  color: var(--color-ink);
  margin: 0 0 16px;
  letter-spacing: -0.01em;
}
.pull-quote cite { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: #6a6577; font-style: normal; }
.follow { margin-top: 32px !important; }

.decision { margin-top: 40px; padding-top: 28px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(var(--color-accent-rgb), 0.2); }
.decision .eyebrow { margin-bottom: 10px; }
.decision h3 {
  font-size: 23px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: -0.015em;
  color: var(--color-ink);
  margin: 0 0 16px;
}
.decision p + p { margin-top: 20px; }

/* ── Wide sections ── */
.wide { max-width: var(--max-nav); margin: 0 auto; padding: 56px var(--gutter) 0; }
.wide-intro { max-width: var(--max-prose); margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 var(--gutter); }
.wide-intro h3 {
  font-size: 24px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: -0.015em;
  color: var(--color-ink);
  margin: 0 0 6px;
}
.wide-intro p { font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.75; color: var(--color-body-soft); margin: 0 0 32px; }

.needs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 20px; }
.need { border-top: 2px solid var(--color-accent); padding-top: 22px; }
.frac { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 600; font-size: 46px; color: var(--color-accent); letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1; }
.need p { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--color-body-soft); margin: 14px 0 0; }
.need strong { font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink); }

.uc-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; }
.uc { background: var(--color-bg-lilac-soft); border: 1px solid rgba(var(--color-accent-rgb), 0.14); border-radius: var(--radius-card); padding: 28px; }
.uc .eyebrow { letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.uc p { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--color-body-soft); margin: 0; }

.solution-head { max-width: var(--max-prose); margin: 0 auto 28px; border-bottom: none; padding-bottom: 0; }
.solution-block { background: var(--color-dark); border-radius: var(--radius-xl); padding: 56px; color: #fff; }
.solution-block p {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-weight: 500;
  font-size: 28px;
  line-height: 1.45;
  letter-spacing: -0.015em;
  margin: 0;
  max-width: 46ch;
}

.impact-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; }
.impact-card { border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 40px; }
.impact-card .stat { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 600; font-size: 64px; line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -0.03em; }
.impact-card p { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; margin: 16px 0 0; }
.impact-card.accent { background: var(--color-accent); color: #fff; }
.impact-card.accent p { opacity: 0.92; }
.impact-card.lilac { background: var(--color-bg-lilac); color: var(--color-ink); }
.impact-card.lilac .stat { color: var(--color-accent); }
.impact-card.lilac p { color: var(--color-muted); }

.next-wrap { padding: 72px var(--gutter) 96px; }
.next-card {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: 24px;
  background: var(--color-bg-cream);
  border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
  border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  padding: 32px 40px;
  transition: background 200ms ease, border-color 200ms ease;
}
.next-card:hover { background: var(--color-bg-lilac); border-color: rgba(var(--color-accent-rgb), 0.3); }
.eyebrow.plain { color: #6a6577; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.next-title { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 600; font-size: 28px; letter-spacing: -0.02em; color: var(--color-ink); }
.next-arrow { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 32px; color: var(--color-accent); }

@media (max-width: 760px) {
  .case-header h1 { font-size: clamp(40px, 11vw, 62px); }
  .meta { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 18px; }
  .needs-grid, .uc-grid, .impact-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .solution-block { padding: 36px; }
  .solution-block p { font-size: 22px; }
}
</style>
